{"metadata":{"role":"article","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Vector Tile Sources"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Add and style a vector tile source"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Styling and Dynamic Data","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/AnimatedLineExample","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/WebAPIDataExample","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/LineStyleLayerExample","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/POIAlongRouteExample","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/GeoJSON","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/PMTiles"],"generated":true}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/DDSCircleLayerExample","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre-native-for-ios\/ddscirclelayerexample"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example uses UIKit"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example shows how a vector data source can be added and a style for it can be configured dynamically."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The tiles are "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/demotiles\/tree\/gh-pages\/tiles-omt","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" that use the OpenMapTiles schema. We are interested in the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/openmaptiles.org\/schema\/#poi","isActive":true},{"text":" that are in the ","type":"text"},{"code":"poi","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" layer, and filter this further with an "},{"code":"NSPredicate","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to only show POIs with a "},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" of shop. Each POI has a "},{"code":"rank","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" which is normally used to reduce label density. In this example, we use it to demonstrate how a numeric attribute can be used for styling with the "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/maplibre.org\/maplibre-style-spec\/expressions\/#step","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" expression. POIs with a rank between 0 and 10 get a red color, between 10 and 20 green, etc.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["class DDSCircleLayerExample: UIViewController, MLNMapViewDelegate {","    var mapView: MLNMapView!","","    override func viewDidLoad() {","        super.viewDidLoad()","","        mapView = MLNMapView(frame: view.bounds, styleURL: AMERICANA_STYLE)","        mapView.autoresizingMask = [.flexibleWidth, .flexibleHeight]","        mapView.tintColor = .darkGray","","        \/\/ Set the mapâ€™s center coordinate and zoom level.","        let innsbruck = CLLocationCoordinate2D(latitude: 47.26497, longitude: 11.4088)","        mapView.setCenter(innsbruck, animated: false)","        mapView.zoomLevel = 14","","        mapView.delegate = self","        view.addSubview(mapView)","    }","","    \/\/ Wait until the style is loaded before modifying the map style.","    func mapView(_: MLNMapView, didFinishLoading style: MLNStyle) {","        let source = MLNVectorTileSource(identifier: \"demotiles\", configurationURL: URL(string: \"https:\/\/demotiles.maplibre.org\/tiles-omt\/tiles.json\")!)","","        style.addSource(source)","","        let layer = MLNCircleStyleLayer(identifier: \"poi-shop-style\", source: source)","","        layer.sourceLayerIdentifier = \"poi\"","        layer.predicate = NSPredicate(format: \"class == %@\", \"shop\")","","        \/\/ Style the circle layer color based on the rank","        layer.circleColor = NSExpression(mglJSONObject: [\"step\", [\"get\", \"rank\"], 0, \"red\", 10, \"green\", 20, \"blue\", 30, \"purple\", 40, \"yellow\"] as [Any])","        layer.circleRadius = NSExpression(forConstantValue: 3)","","        style.addLayer(layer)","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"DDSCircleLayerExample.png"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Map data from OpenStreetMap. Style uses OpenMapTiles."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS/PMTiles":{"type":"topic","title":"PMTiles","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre-native-for-ios\/pmtiles","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/PMTiles","role":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Working with PMTiles","type":"text"}],"kind":"article"},"https://maplibre.org/maplibre-style-spec/expressions/#step":{"url":"https:\/\/maplibre.org\/maplibre-style-spec\/expressions\/#step","type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/maplibre.org\/maplibre-style-spec\/expressions\/#step","title":"step","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"step","type":"text"}]},"https://openmaptiles.org/schema/#poi":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"POIs"}],"title":"POIs","type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/openmaptiles.org\/schema\/#poi","url":"https:\/\/openmaptiles.org\/schema\/#poi"},"https://github.com/maplibre/demotiles/tree/gh-pages/tiles-omt":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/demotiles\/tree\/gh-pages\/tiles-omt","type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/demotiles\/tree\/gh-pages\/tiles-omt","title":"tiles around Innsbruck, Austria","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"tiles around Innsbruck, Austria","type":"text"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"title":"MapLibre","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and